To formulate a novel proposal, I propose an idea that builds upon the concept of inter-layer dependencies in mixed-precision quantization while introducing a unique approach that emphasizes a training-free, geometric perspective on quantization. This new framework will leverage curvature-aware diagnostics to determine optimal precision allocations across layers based on geometric properties of the loss landscape.

Here’s the refined proposal:

