    "Title": "Geometric Mixed-Precision Quantization: A Training-Free Approach Leveraging Curvature Diagnostics",
    "Short Hypothesis": "Can we utilize curvature-aware diagnostics in the loss landscape to derive optimal mixed-precision quantization strategies that are training-free and maintain accuracy across varying model architectures?",
    "Related Work": "While existing work focuses on training-based or heuristic methods for mixed-precision quantization, our approach uniquely employs geometric principles and curvature diagnostics to inform precision allocation across layers. This contrasts with current methods that often overlook inter-layer dependencies and do not leverage the geometric properties of the loss landscape.",
    "Abstract": "The deployment of large-scale machine learning models necessitates efficient quantization techniques to balance computational efficiency and model accuracy. Traditional mixed-precision quantization methods either rely heavily on extensive training or heuristic rules, which can lead to suboptimal results. In this proposal, we introduce a novel training-free framework for mixed-precision quantization that leverages curvature-aware diagnostics derived from the loss landscape. By analyzing the geometric properties of the model’s loss function, we can identify critical regions where precision can be reduced without significantly impacting performance. This approach allows for a more informed allocation of bit-widths across model layers, enabling optimal quantization configurations that adapt to model architecture while ensuring stability and accuracy. We will validate our framework through rigorous empirical evaluations on benchmark datasets, providing insights into the robustness and efficiency of our geometric approach.",
