    "Related Work": "Existing mixed precision quantization methods, such as EMQ and InfoQ, rely on heuristic-based or evolutionary strategies that do not fully leverage the mathematical structure of neural networks. This proposal distinguishes itself by grounding quantization strategies in linear algebraic principles, particularly focusing on the geometric properties of weight distributions to inform bit-width allocation.",
    "Abstract": "In this work, we propose a novel approach to mixed precision quantization that harnesses the intrinsic geometric structures of neural network weights to derive deterministic quantization strategies. By applying linear algebraic techniques, particularly Singular Value Decomposition (SVD), we aim to identify the critical weight components that contribute to model performance. This method will allow us to create quantization schemas based on the significance of these components, leading to efficient mixed precision deployment without the need for retraining. Our approach will be empirically validated through a series of experiments across various neural network architectures, demonstrating improved accuracy-computation trade-offs in comparison to existing heuristic methods. The proposed framework not only enhances efficiency but also ensures mathematical transparency and reproducibility.",
    "Experiments": [
      "Conduct experiments on standard datasets (e.g., ImageNet) using various neural architectures (e.g., ResNet, ViT) to validate the proposed geometric quantization framework.",
