### Proposal Reflection and Refinement

#### Novelty and Quality:
The proposed idea seeks to explore the geometric properties of mixed-precision quantization by utilizing curvature-aware routing protocols to explicitly connect the quantization process with the underlying manifold structure of the neural network's weight space. This approach would not only refine the existing training-free methods but also provide a more profound theoretical foundation by incorporating curvature analysis. Thus, it stands out from existing works, which often focus on empirical performance without a solid geometric rationale.

#### Feasibility:
The proposal remains feasible within the constraints of a single-GPU setup, leveraging existing computational resources. The implementation of curvature-aware diagnostics and geometric probes can be accomplished without extensive hardware upgrades, aligning well with the methodological preferences outlined.

#### Clarity and Conciseness:
The proposal is clear in its objectives and methodology, aiming to establish a new framework that integrates geometric insights into the quantization process. It outlines specific experiments and evaluation metrics that are straightforward to implement and analyze.

### Refined Proposal

