    "Related Work": "This proposal builds on existing works like SliM-LLM and FlexiQ by introducing dynamic quantization that adapts in real-time to workload fluctuations, rather than applying a static strategy or a pre-defined scheme. While previous methods focus on fixed bit-width allocations, our approach emphasizes adaptability based on current operational conditions, making it more suitable for edge computing scenarios where resource availability can vary rapidly.",
