Based on the recent literature search and existing proposals, I propose a refined research idea that focuses on bridging the gap between existing mixed-precision quantization frameworks and the need for robustness in low-resource environments without extensive retraining. This proposal targets the emerging challenges in quantization strategies, particularly in the context of deployment on edge devices.

Here is the finalized proposal:

IDEA JSON:
```json
{
  "idea": {
    "Name": "adaptive_router_mixed_precision",
    "Title": "Adaptive Router for Robust Mixed-Precision Quantization in Edge Deployments",
    "Short Hypothesis": "Can we develop a training-free adaptive routing mechanism that dynamically selects precision levels for each layer of a neural network, optimizing for robustness against quantization errors and resource constraints in edge devices?",
    "Related Work": "Existing frameworks, such as EMQ and AMP-ViT, have made strides in mixed-precision quantization. However, they often rely on heuristic approaches or extensive tuning to manage trade-offs between accuracy and efficiency, and they lack a robust dynamic adaptation mechanism that accounts for varying resource constraints in edge environments. Our proposal distinguishes itself by introducing a training-free adaptive routing protocol that utilizes real-time diagnostics to inform precision adjustments, ensuring operational robustness without requiring extensive retraining.",
    "Abstract": "As deep learning models become increasingly prevalent on resource-constrained edge devices, the challenge of optimizing mixed-precision quantization grows more critical. Current methods often rely on heuristic or static strategies that fail to adapt dynamically to changing conditions, resulting in suboptimal performance. This proposal introduces an innovative adaptive router framework for mixed-precision quantization that leverages real-time diagnostic metrics to make informed precision decisions at runtime. By employing a training-free approach that integrates curvature-aware diagnostics and stability bounds, our framework ensures that precision levels are dynamically adjusted based on the operational context, thus promoting robustness and efficiency. We will validate our approach through a series of experiments comparing our framework against existing state-of-the-art methods, focusing on quantization accuracy, computational overhead, and adaptability to varying resource constraints. The proposed work aims to push the boundaries of mixed-precision quantization, providing a scalable solution tailored for edge deployments.",
    "Experiments": [
      "1. Implement a baseline mixed-precision quantization framework to establish performance metrics.",
      "2. Develop the adaptive routing mechanism, utilizing real-time diagnostics (gradient covariance decay, Hessian conditioning) to inform layer precision dynamically.",
      "3. Evaluate the accuracy and efficiency of the adaptive router compared to baseline and existing methods on standard datasets like ImageNet.",
      "4. Conduct ablation studies to isolate the impact of different diagnostic metrics on routing decisions.",
      "5. Measure the computational overhead and resource consumption during inference to quantify operational efficiency."
    ],
    "Risk Factors and Limitations": [
      "The adaptive routing mechanism may introduce latency if real-time diagnostics are computationally expensive.",
      "Performance may vary significantly across different architectures and datasets, limiting generalizability.",
      "Without careful tuning, the dynamic adjustments might lead to instability in model performance."
    ]
  }
}
```

In this refined proposal, I have focused on developing a robust adaptive router for mixed-precision quantization that addresses the limitations of existing frameworks such as EMQ and AMP-ViT. By emphasizing training-free dynamics and real-time diagnostics, this proposal aims to fill a critical gap in the literature while remaining grounded in feasible experimental designs and clear evaluation metrics.
