      "Existing quantization and pruning methods may limit the applicability of the proposed framework if they do not adhere to the derived principles.",
      "The complexity of deriving tight bounds may lead to increased computational overhead in the experimental phase."
    ]
  }
}

This refined proposal explicitly connects the principles of rate-distortion theory to practical implementations in neural network compression while remaining grounded in rigorous information-theoretic frameworks. It is feasible within an academic lab setting and aims to bridge theoretical insights with practical outcomes, ensuring both publishability and relevance to current research trends in machine learning.
