The idea is to explore an information-theoretic framework for adaptive bit-width allocation in mixed-precision quantization that directly ties the bit allocation to statistical measures of task-relevant information and distortion rates. This approach will focus on deriving bounds on the achievable rates for different layers of a neural network based on their contribution to model performance, assessed through mutual information.

### Proposal

