    "Related Work": "While previous works like 'An Information-Theoretic Justification for Model Pruning' and 'AMP-ViT' have examined pruning and quantization separately, they do not combine both approaches into a unified framework. This proposal distinguishes itself by deriving a joint rate-distortion formulation that considers the interaction between pruning and quantization, allowing for a more nuanced understanding and optimization of model compression.",
    "Abstract": "This research proposes a novel information-theoretic framework for model compression that integrates pruning and quantization as a singular rate-distortion optimization problem. Leveraging the principles of rate-distortion theory, we aim to derive new bounds and strategies that capture the interplay between model sparsity and quantization granularity. By explicitly modeling how pruning affects the distribution of quantized weights and vice versa, we will establish theoretical insights into the achievable compression rates while maintaining task-relevant performance. Initial experiments will test the proposed framework on benchmark datasets, evaluating the performance of combined methods against traditional separate approaches. This integrated approach not only aims to improve the efficiency of model compression but also to contribute to the theoretical understanding of the limits of such methods.",
