Based on the recent literature, it is evident that there is a growing interest in mixed-precision quantization and its impact on efficiency and performance for various models, including large language models (LLMs) and vision transformers (ViTs). However, many existing works primarily focus on either layer-wise sensitivity or automatic optimization frameworks without fully addressing the on-device performance implications of quantization strategies. 

With these insights, I propose a novel research idea that builds upon the existing frameworks but emphasizes hardware-level profiling and real-world performance metrics to evaluate the efficiency of mixed-precision quantization in LLMs. The key innovation is to develop a GPU kernel specifically optimized for mixed-precision quantization while incorporating a profiling mechanism that dynamically adjusts quantization levels based on real-time performance feedback. This approach seeks to bridge the gap between theoretical efficiency and practical implementation.

### Revised Proposal

