  "idea": {
    "Name": "dynamic_kernel_adaptation",
    "Title": "Dynamic Kernel Adaptation for Optimized GPU Resource Allocation in ML Inference",
    "Short Hypothesis": "Dynamic adaptation of GPU kernels based on real-time workload characteristics can significantly enhance resource utilization and reduce latency in ML inference tasks.",
    "Related Work": "Current approaches, such as Astra and KRISP, focus on static optimization or model-wise partitioning, which do not adequately address the dynamic nature of inference workloads. This proposal distinguishes itself by introducing a real-time, kernel-wise adaptation mechanism that tailors kernel execution to the current workload, thereby enabling more efficient GPU resource utilization.",
    "Abstract": "As machine learning inference workloads continue to grow in complexity, the need for efficient GPU resource allocation becomes increasingly critical. Existing optimization methods often rely on static heuristics that fail to account for the dynamic nature of these workloads. In this proposal, we introduce a novel approach to dynamic kernel adaptation, which leverages real-time profiling data to tailor GPU kernel execution based on the specific characteristics of incoming inference requests. By monitoring key performance metrics such as occupancy, memory bandwidth usage, and kernel execution time, we will adaptively select and optimize kernel configurations on-the-fly. This approach aims to achieve significant reductions in latency and improved resource utilization compared to current static methods. We will conduct experiments to validate the effectiveness of this method across various machine learning models, including large language models, and report improvements in throughput and energy efficiency.",
    "Experiments": [
      "Set up a baseline using existing static kernel configurations for common ML inference tasks.",
      "Implement a dynamic profiling system to monitor real-time workload characteristics during inference.",
      "Develop a kernel adaptation mechanism that selects optimal configurations based on the monitored metrics.",
      "Conduct A/B testing between static and dynamic configurations while measuring p50/p99 latency, throughput under batching, and energy per token.",
      "Evaluate performance across multiple GPUs with different architectures to assess generalizability."
    ],
