### Proposal Refinement

**Research Idea:** The idea is to develop a new framework for compression in neural networks based on an information-theoretic perspective that combines quantization and pruning, optimized through a rate-distortion approach. This framework will focus on deriving quantitative bounds on the achievable compression rates while maintaining task-relevant performance.

**Novelty and Distinction:** While there are existing works addressing model pruning and quantization from an information-theoretic perspective (like the ones identified), many of them either lack a comprehensive quantitative framework or do not effectively integrate both quantization and pruning within the same theoretical structure. This proposal emphasizes a unified approach that not only derives achievable rates but also provides a systematic methodology for evaluating distortion in relation to task performance.

**Feasibility:** The experiments proposed will involve standard datasets and accessible evaluation metrics that can be implemented without requiring excessive resources. The theoretical framework will be grounded in established rate-distortion theory, ensuring practical applicability while maintaining an academic rigor.

### Final Proposal

