Given the existing body of work, I propose a novel research idea that aims to bridge these gaps by exploring a new method for adaptive quantization informed by information-theoretic principles. This proposal leverages concepts of mutual information and relevant distortion measures to dynamically allocate precision in a way that maximizes task performance while minimizing the overall bit-cost, thus aligning with your methodological preferences.

