l quantization scheme based on rate-distortion principles and mutual information metrics.', '2. Implement the derived quantization strategy on benchmark neural network architectures (e.g., ResNet, ViTs) and compare performance with existing methods such as AMP-ViT and SNIP.', '3. Evaluate model performance using standard metrics like accuracy and F1-score against various compression ratios.', '4. Analyze the relationship between bit allocation, model accuracy, and the achieved distortion rates through empirical testing.'], 'Risk Factors and Limitations': 'Potential risks include the challenge of accurately estimating mutual information in high-dimensional spaces, which may lead to practical implementation difficulties. Additionally, the adaptive quantization approach may require extensive tuning to achieve optimal performance, which could introduce variability in results. Lastly, the proposed method will need to be validated across multiple architectures to ensure generalizability.'}
